      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., ASME V&V 20 validation metric or equivalent) applied to QoIs with explicit acceptance threshold.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and yield load compared using mean absolute percentage error (MAPE). MAPE for stiffness: 3.8%; MAPE for yield load: 4.2%. Both within pre-specified 10% acceptance threshold. Statistical equivalence confirmed."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield load) directly linked to the clinical question of construct mechanical integrity.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and yield load under compression-bending are the primary mechanical performance indicators for posterior lumbar fixation per ASTM F1717. These QoIs are directly relevant to the intended use of the FEA model in supporting 510(k) submissions."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
